Aston Villa have qualified for the final of this seasonâ€™s Carabao Cup. The Midlands club defeated Leicester City 2-1, in the second leg of their semi-final tie on Tuesday night. With the score delicately poised at 1-1, both teams came into the match at Villa Park with a chance to progress. Jack Grealish set up Matt Targett to smash a shot past Kasper Schmeichel to make it 1-0, before Kelechi Iheanacho equalized in the 72nd minute. Trezeguet then scored a dramatic late winner as Villa edged it 3-2 on aggregate. Five-times winners Villa will face either Manchester United or Manchester City, who play in the other semi-final on Wednesday.